- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with the semantics of concurrent programs and introduces a new notion of non-positive curvature, which is a logical concept. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper uses precubical sets, which are a combinatorial tool in algebraic topology, to study the geometry of the space of possible executions of the program. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is likely because the paper studies the geometry of the space of possible executions of the program and uses the notion of curvature to characterize it. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is likely because the paper studies the geometric realization of precubical sets in metric spaces, which is a topic related to computer graphics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible because the paper deals with synchronization primitives in concurrent programs, which is a topic related to control systems.
